Third-party notices
===================

This project vendors one third-party component and interoperates with others
at run time. Users are responsible for honouring each license.

Vendored (shipped with this repository)
---------------------------------------

- **BiSeNet architecture code**, in ``src/hairtone/_vendor/bisenet/``, is a
  clean inference-only subset of
  https://github.com/zllrunning/face-parsing.PyTorch, released under the
  **MIT License**. The verbatim upstream LICENSE text is preserved in
  ``licenses/zllrunning-MIT.txt``.

User-downloaded at run time (NOT shipped)
-----------------------------------------

- **SegFormer face-parsing checkpoint** (HuggingFace
  ``jonathandinu/face-parsing``) — per its HuggingFace model card, released
  **for non-commercial research and educational purposes only**. The model
  is fine-tuned from ``nvidia/mit-b5`` (which carries NVIDIA's own
  restrictions) on the **CelebAMask-HQ** dataset (research-only).
  Commercial use requires replacing this checkpoint (either retrain on a
  permissive dataset or plug in a different backend via the
  ``HairtoneBackend`` protocol).

- **BiSeNet CelebAMask-HQ checkpoint** (e.g.
  ``zllrunning/face-parsing.PyTorch`` ``79999_iter.pth``) — distributed
  under **MIT**, but its training data (CelebAMask-HQ) is research-only.

Python dependencies at run time
-------------------------------

- **transformers** (``huggingface/transformers``) — Apache 2.0.
- **torch** — BSD-3-Clause (with component-specific licences).
- **opencv-python** — Apache 2.0 (with third-party notices).
- **numpy** — BSD-3-Clause.
- **Pillow** — HPND.

Check each project's own LICENSE file for the authoritative terms.
